The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Maoists shot
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Maoists shot
                            
	Midnapore, Jan. 2: Three alleged Maoists were killed today in an encounter with police 12km from Jhargram town.        
	When a 200-strong force approached Joynagar village, nearly 1,000 people blocked their path. The Maoists used the villagers as shields and hid themselves behind, said district police chief Manoj Verma.        
	While being surrounded, officers saw through binoculars men with AK-47s in the village. When the police used tear gas to disperse the crowd, the Maoists started firing.         
	After the firing stopped at 5pm, Bijoy Mahato, 24, and Bhola Mahato, 43, were found dead. Rakhal Rana, 45, died later.         
	The police said they were wanted Maoists.                                                                                                                                                            
